channel.title: A compiler for jdk u7?
channel.description:
well im always tryin to compile my work and i cant because apparently its not compatible with my version of jdk so i was wondering if someone could give me the link or even just the code to a compatible compiler? help would be much appreciated. thanx
~Vamp
EDIT: someone helped me out sry yall thanx.

item.title: A compiler for jdk u7?
item.dc:creator: @_Paranoia †Paranoia†
item.description:
@_Paranoia wrote:

@echo off
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit
